2.	Simple queries with MongoDB
>use school

**create:-
>db.students.insertMany([{name:"Aarchie",age:20,rollno:22},{name:"Tanvi",age:21,rollno:07},
{name:"Ravi",age:18,rollno:33},{name:"Vikrant",age:22,rollno:06}])

**update age of someone:-
>db.students.updateOne({name:"Aarchie"},{$set:{age:21}})
 
 **update the one’s having age 21 to 25
>db.students.updateMany({age:21},{$set:{age:25}})
 

**show that the one’s having age 18 is not eligible
>db.students.updateMany({age:18},{$set:{age:"Not Eligible"}})
 

**age>=21 are eligible
>db.students.updateMany({age:{$gte:21}},{$set:{"is eligible:":true}})
 
**delete someone’s name
>db.students.deleteOne({name:”Tanvi”})
 

**delete the one’s having age 18
>db.students.deleteMany({age:"Not Eligible"})
